### AI Notes Management System API Testing Examples
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api

### 1. Get Paginated Notes (Latest first, page 1, 10 per page)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notes?page=1&limit=10
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Create Note
# Note: Generates vector embedding in background/sync during save
POST {{baseUrl}}/notes
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "title": "Clean Code and SOLID Principles",
  "content": "SOLID is a mnemonic acronym for five design principles intended to make software designs more understandable, flexible, and maintainable. Single responsibility, Open-closed, Liskov substitution, Interface segregation, and Dependency inversion."
}

###

### 3. Get Single Note (Replace ID with an actual note ID, e.g., 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notes/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Update Note (Replace ID with an actual note ID)
# Note: Re-calculates embedding, invalidates cached note summary
PUT {{baseUrl}}/notes/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "title": "Clean Code and SOLID Principles (Updated)",
  "content": "SOLID is a mnemonic acronym for five design principles intended to make software designs more understandable, flexible, and maintainable. 1. Single Responsibility. 2. Open-Closed. 3. Liskov Substitution. 4. Interface Segregation. 5. Dependency Inversion."
}

###

### 5. Generate AI Summary for Note (Replace ID with actual ID)
# Note: Hits OpenAI on first call, caches output in Redis for subsequent requests
POST {{baseUrl}}/notes/1/summary
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Semantic Search Notes
# Note: Converts query to vector embedding, computes cosine similarity against notes
POST {{baseUrl}}/notes/search
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "explain design principles for clean software architectures"
}

###

### 7. Delete Note (Replace ID with actual ID)
# Note: Deletes note and invalidates Redis cached summary
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/notes/1
Accept: application/json
